        "Name": "Longbow II",
        "Details": "A rebuild of the venerable LGB-7Q Longbow that increases its weight by more than 40 per cent, the Longbow II is a veritable walking arsenal. Unlike the 9, the 10 replaces the launch tubes with a huge array of SRMs along with a set of accelerating launch rails for improved range and some Large X-Pulse Lasers to provide direct fire support. The Longbow II also mounts enough heat dissipation capacity to fire all its weapons without significantly heating up. This superheavy 'Mech was first produced by the Free Worlds League, but the design has since spread to most parts of the Inner Sphere, whether by capture or trade.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
